    <stitle>530 and DT-466/408 Diesel Engine Service (1994) - VIBRATION DAMPER, CRANKSHAFT, MAIN BEARINGS, FLYWHEEL AND
        CRANKCASE - REAR OIL SEAL AND WEAR SLEEVE - REAR OIL SEAL AND WEAR SLEEVE INSTALLATION
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="proctype" graphiccount="2">
        <title>REAR OIL SEAL AND WEAR SLEEVE INSTALLATION</title>
        <svcprocinfo>
            <specpara>
                <important>
                    <para>INSTALL THE REAR OIL SEAL AND WEAR SLEEVE AS A UNIT. DO NOT REMOVE THE SEAL FROM THE WEAR
                        SLEEVE PRIOR TO INSTALLATION.
                    </para>
                </important>
            </specpara>
        </svcprocinfo>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install a new rear oil seal and crankshaft wear sleeve assembly using the installer tool
                <emph type="bold">ZTSE4374b</emph>
                as follows:
            </para>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Clean crankshaft flange and flywheel housing bore throughly. Remove any debris.</para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Attach guide and secure with two (2) mounting screws (
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef1050718">7.18</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    ).
                </para>
                <figure id="ef1050717" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="eg3060" filename="../figeg3/EG3060.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 7.17.</caption>
                    <calloutgroup>
                        <callout1>1. Hammer</callout1>
                        <callout1>2. Wear Sleeve</callout1>
                        <callout1>3. Crankshaft</callout1>
                        <callout1>4. Crankcase</callout1>
                    </calloutgroup>
                </figure>
                <figure id="ef1050718" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="eg3118" filename="../figeg3/EG3118.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 7.18.</caption>
                    <calloutgroup>
                        <callout1>1. Crankcase</callout1>
                        <callout1>2. Rear Oil Seal Carrier</callout1>
                        <callout1>3. Guide</callout1>
                    </calloutgroup>
                </figure>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Coat inner I.D. of wear sleeve and O.D. of oil seal with Aviation Permatex.</para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Position oil seal and wear sleeve over crankshaft (
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk document="e105_141.xml" xrefid="ef1050719">7.19</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    ).
                </para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Assemble wear sleeve/oil seal installer tool onto crankshaft. Turn forcing nut on
                    installer tool until seal and sleeve are seated in the bore (
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk document="e105_141.xml" xrefid="ef1050720">7.20</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    ).
                </para>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>Proper use of the installer tool will assure that the seal and wear sleeve are pressed
                            onto the crankshaft flange to the proper depth.
                        </para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
            </step2>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
